151
00:08:54,555 --> 00:08:56,714
- This morning-
- I'm pregnant.

152
00:09:02,394 --> 00:09:04,273
I'm sure.

153
00:09:09,992 --> 00:09:13,592
Well, that's-
That's very surprising.

154
00:09:15,872 --> 00:09:18,511
Does Walter know that, uh-

155
00:09:18,591 --> 00:09:21,911
I think Walter would find this
a little more than surprising.

156
00:09:31,310 --> 00:09:34,149
Emily left me this morning.

157
00:09:34,229 --> 00:09:36,229
She's left before.

158
00:09:36,309 --> 00:09:39,628
She's left the room before,
but she's always come back.

159
00:09:43,268 --> 00:09:45,108
So.

160
00:09:46,987 --> 00:09:49,587
I guess we just divorce
our spouses, marry each other...

161
00:09:49,627 --> 00:09:52,147
and have this baby, right?

162
00:09:52,187 --> 00:09:54,067
Simple.

163
00:09:54,107 --> 00:09:56,346
Yeah, right. Simple.

164
00:10:02,425 --> 00:10:04,625
Is that Cristalle?

165
00:10:04,705 --> 00:10:07,065
- Mm-hmm.
- Oh, God.

166
00:10:07,145 --> 00:10:10,504
I wear the same scent
as a transvestite.

167
00:10:10,584 --> 00:10:12,464
She is a transvestite,
isn't she?

168
00:10:12,504 --> 00:10:15,064
If she's not now,
Terry'll make sure she is...

169
00:10:15,144 --> 00:10:17,023
by the end of the evening.

170
00:10:17,103 --> 00:10:19,663
Has he asked you
about the book yet?

171
00:10:19,703 --> 00:10:21,623
Yes.

172
00:10:21,743 --> 00:10:23,583
And?

173
00:10:24,862 --> 00:10:27,622
Are you gonna tell him?

174
00:10:27,662 --> 00:10:32,661
No. Maybe. I don't know
what I'm gonna do.

175
00:10:32,741 --> 00:10:35,341
Me either.

