00:10:35,461 --> 00:10:37,261
DiMaggio's record...

177
00:10:37,341 --> 00:10:39,180
for hits in consecutive games...

178
00:10:39,260 --> 00:10:41,380
is probably the most impressive
feat in all of sports...

179
00:10:41,460 --> 00:10:43,380
and in my opinion,
will never be broken.

180
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:46,179
- Come here, big guy.
- His condition's so sad.

181
00:10:46,219 --> 00:10:48,419
Yes, but even blind,
he still gets around.

182
00:10:48,459 --> 00:10:51,899
I don't drink normally...

183
00:10:51,979 --> 00:10:55,418
but this was turning out to be
one fucked-up day.

184
00:10:55,498 --> 00:10:59,578
And now I found myself in close
proximity to Sara's husband...

185
00:10:59,658 --> 00:11:02,057
and his dog, Poe.

186
00:11:02,137 --> 00:11:04,577
- Walter, I see you've met my friend.
- Oh, yes. She's charming.

187
00:11:04,657 --> 00:11:06,977
Despite his much-vaunted
Harvard education...

188
00:11:07,017 --> 00:11:10,616
Dr. Walter Gaskell didn't have
a clue about his wife and me.

189
00:11:10,696 --> 00:11:13,376
Simply put, Di Maggio represented-
metaphorically speaking, of course-

190
00:11:13,416 --> 00:11:15,295
the husband as slugger.

191
00:11:15,335 --> 00:11:17,735
Poe had been
on to me since day one.

192
00:11:17,775 --> 00:11:20,215
In fact, I personally believe...

193
00:11:20,295 --> 00:11:24,614
that every woman in some way
desires to be Marilyn Monroe.

194
00:11:24,694 --> 00:11:27,014
Oh, I couldn't agree more.

195
00:11:27,094 --> 00:11:30,213
I've had a lot
of successes over the years.

196
00:11:30,253 --> 00:11:33,533
Q. Q was rich.

197
00:11:33,573 --> 00:11:35,493
Q was famous.

198
00:11:35,533 --> 00:11:38,212
Q completed a novel
every 18 months.

199
00:11:38,252 --> 00:11:40,132
I hated him.

200
00:11:40,212 --> 00:11:42,372
...finest work vanished
in less than five.

201
00:11:42,412 --> 00:11:45,091
So I find myself conflicted.

202
00:11:45,171 --> 00:11:48,531
Ask him if he's conflicted
about his house in the Hamptons.

203
00:11:48,611 --> 00:11:51,491
- Grady.
- Well, Professor.

204
00:11:51,531 --> 00:11:52,770
Q. for your information...

205
00:11:52,850 --> 00:11:54,650
Hannah already has
two stories published...

206
00:11:54,690 --> 00:11:58,930
in The Paris Review, so you
better dust off your "A" material.

207
00:11:59,010 --> 00:12:02,089
You didn't tell me
you were a writer.

208
00:12:02,169 --> 00:12:03,569
You didn't ask.

209
00:12:03,649 --> 00:12:05,529
How did you feel
about the adaptation?

210
00:12:05,569 --> 00:12:07,488
I thought it was more literary
than cinematic.

211
00:12:07,608 --> 00:12:08,728
Grady.

212
00:12:08,768 --> 00:12:11,008
Douglas Triddley, Amherst.

213
00:12:11,048 --> 00:12:12,208
I've had Arsonist's Daughter...

214
00:12:12,288 --> 00:12:14,647
on my graduate-studies syllabus
three years running.

215
00:12:14,687 --> 00:12:17,047
No wonder it's still in print.

216
00:12:18,527 --> 00:12:20,407
Long time since
Arsonist's Daughter.

217
00:12:38,684 --> 00:12:40,564
There you are.

218
00:12:40,604 --> 00:12:45,843
I could have sworn I had a bottle
of 1975 Lafite Rothschild for Q.

219
00:12:45,923 --> 00:12:47,803
Given that he's going to be
addressing 500 people...

220
00:12:47,923 --> 00:12:49,283
in less than an hour-

221
00:12:49,363 --> 00:12:51,962
- You want to keep Q happy.
- If he's happy, I'm happy.

222
00:13:12,040 --> 00:13:14,159
James?

223
00:13:17,959 --> 00:13:20,798
It's fake.
It was my mother's.

224
00:13:20,838 --> 00:13:23,678
She won it in a penny arcade
in Baltimore...

225
00:13:23,718 --> 00:13:25,678
when she went
to Catholic school.

226
00:13:26,878 --> 00:13:29,437
Well, that's very convincing.

227
00:13:29,477 --> 00:13:32,157
I used to shoot
these little paper caps...

228
00:13:32,197 --> 00:13:34,557
but they don't make them anymore,
the caps.

229
00:13:34,597 --> 00:13:38,156
It's just for good luck, you know?
Some people carry rabbit's feet.

230
00:13:38,236 --> 00:13:40,596
You carry firearms.

231
00:13:42,396 --> 00:13:46,235
No, thank you. I don't like
to lose control of my emotions.

232
00:13:47,915 --> 00:13:50,714
I'm not supposed to be here,
in case you're wondering.

233
00:13:50,794 --> 00:13:53,434
But the other night I was out
with Hannah at the movies...

234
00:13:53,474 --> 00:13:57,833
and she asked me since she was
coming, so I ended up coming too.

235
00:13:57,913 --> 00:13:59,993
You and, uh, Hannah,
you're seeing each other?

236
00:14:00,073 --> 00:14:02,913
- No! What gave you that idea?
- James, relax.

237
00:14:03,033 --> 00:14:05,272
I'm not her father.
I just rent her a room.

238
00:14:05,312 --> 00:14:08,152
She likes old movies like I do,
that's all.

239
00:14:08,192 --> 00:14:10,872
- What's the movie you guys saw?
- Son of Fury...

240
00:14:10,912 --> 00:14:13,231
with Tyrone Power
and Frances Farmer.

241
00:14:14,231 --> 00:14:16,871
She went crazy,
Frances Farmer.

242
00:14:16,951 --> 00:14:19,311
So did Gene Tierney.
She's in it too.

243
00:14:20,430 --> 00:14:22,710
- Sounds like a good one.
- It wasn't bad.

244
00:14:25,750 --> 00:14:28,149
You're not like
my other teachers, Prof. Tripp.

245
00:14:28,269 --> 00:14:31,189
