It's just a matter of time.

1092
01:10:01,337 --> 01:10:03,057
Come on.
You don't even know James.

1093
01:10:03,137 --> 01:10:04,417
Who does?

1094
01:10:04,497 --> 01:10:07,456
I do. I do now.

1095
01:10:07,536 --> 01:10:09,576
I spent some time
with him...

1096
01:10:09,656 --> 01:10:11,656
and I read
something of his.

1097
01:10:11,736 --> 01:10:14,176
- His book? You read his book?
- Yes.

1098
01:10:14,216 --> 01:10:16,735
- Is it good?
- It's good. It's very, very good.

1099
01:10:16,775 --> 01:10:20,495
It's-It's true.

1100
01:10:20,535 --> 01:10:23,294
I knew it.
So where is he now?

1101
01:10:23,374 --> 01:10:25,334
I sent him home
with his parents.

1102
01:10:25,414 --> 01:10:28,214
What? What?
His parents?

1103
01:10:28,294 --> 01:10:30,893
- Mm-hmm.
- Why? Why did you do that for?

1104
01:10:30,933 --> 01:10:32,813
Because under
the circumstances...

1105
01:10:32,853 --> 01:10:35,693
I thought it was
the best thing for him, but...

1106
01:10:35,773 --> 01:10:40,292
I'm beginning to think maybe
it was the best thing for me.

1107
01:10:42,092 --> 01:10:45,411
I just, uh-
I wasn't there for him.

1108
01:10:45,451 --> 01:10:48,331
Imagine that.

1109
01:10:48,411 --> 01:10:51,690
Hannah, don't you remember
where you took James that day?

