01:10:51,770 --> 01:10:53,610
Was it his aunt's?

1111
01:10:53,690 --> 01:10:55,730
- Yes.
- I told you. Sewickley Heights.

1112
01:10:55,810 --> 01:10:57,650
- What was the address?
- Mm-hmm.

1113
01:10:57,730 --> 01:10:59,889
I don't know. He had me
drop him on a corner.

1114
01:10:59,929 --> 01:11:01,569
Call the university.
I'm sure they know his address.

1115
01:11:01,649 --> 01:11:03,209
Little late to call Ad missions.

1116
01:11:03,249 --> 01:11:06,168
Is it a little late to call
the chancellor, hmm?

1117
01:11:06,248 --> 01:11:08,088
- I don't know. Maybe.
- Hmm?

1118
01:11:08,168 --> 01:11:10,048
God, you really have just made
an awful...

1119
01:11:10,088 --> 01:11:12,008
stinky little mess
of everything, haven't you?

1120
01:11:14,287 --> 01:11:16,967
Is that it?

1121
01:11:17,047 --> 01:11:18,447
Do not even think about it.

1122
01:11:18,487 --> 01:11:19,927
- Don't go near it.
- No, no, no.

1123
01:11:20,007 --> 01:11:22,286
Never without your permission,
but that is a lot of book.

1124
01:11:22,326 --> 01:11:24,086
262 Baxter Drive.

1125
01:11:24,166 --> 01:11:26,446
They're in the book.

1126
01:11:26,486 --> 01:11:28,525
- I'll drive.
- I'll drive.

1127
01:11:28,645 --> 01:11:30,445
"The Love Parade. "

